WEBVTT

00:01.602 --> 00:03.336
I hurt someone.
I put a pillow over her face.

00:03.338 --> 00:05.070
You can't be here, Andrew.

00:05.072 --> 00:06.805
[ Sobbing ]

00:06.807 --> 00:08.007
Hey.

00:08.009 --> 00:10.009
Hi, Amy.

00:10.011 --> 00:11.010
Who's that?

00:11.012 --> 00:14.013
He's just a fr--
a kid from my skate park.

00:14.015 --> 00:15.948
It was good to see you,
Andrew.

00:15.950 --> 00:18.283
You can't be here.
Noah's back.

00:18.285 --> 00:20.152
Do you want me to leave?

00:21.822 --> 00:23.022
You dealing again?

00:23.024 --> 00:24.557
This is about me
making my own money!

00:24.559 --> 00:26.559
I didn't know you'd also be
a shitty mother.

00:26.561 --> 00:28.561
Renn left and took Nick.

00:28.563 --> 00:29.562
Well, she'll come back.

00:29.564 --> 00:30.963
Yeah, I don't know.

00:30.965 --> 00:32.097
Come on.

00:32.099 --> 00:34.033
♪♪

00:34.035 --> 00:35.634
You were supposed
to meet me tonight.

00:35.636 --> 00:38.170
I got sidetracked
watching TV.

00:38.172 --> 00:40.906
Don't you ever
let it happen again.

00:40.908 --> 00:42.641
What, do you got, like,
a convenience store to rob?

00:42.643 --> 00:44.243
You know what, man?
You need to check

00:44.245 --> 00:46.645
your leader-of-the-pack bullshit
you're playing now.

00:46.647 --> 00:48.647
♪♪

00:48.649 --> 00:49.982
It's got the gate code

00:49.984 --> 00:51.717
and where the cameras are
and everything.

00:51.719 --> 00:52.918
This is great, Taylor.

00:52.920 --> 00:54.453
Good.
'Cause I'm done.

00:54.455 --> 00:59.458
♪♪

01:00.327 --> 01:03.796
♪♪

01:03.798 --> 01:09.735
♪ She stares deeply ♪

01:09.737 --> 01:13.672
♪ Locked inside me ♪

01:13.674 --> 01:16.742
♪ Burnin' brightly ♪

01:19.680 --> 01:25.150
♪ One they know
that I cannot take ♪

01:25.152 --> 01:28.754
♪ Waitin' for it all to begin ♪

01:28.756 --> 01:31.991
♪ Every night now, they'll win ♪

01:35.763 --> 01:38.431
♪ Come and meet my black hole ♪

01:38.433 --> 01:42.501
♪ Got a big black hole ♪

01:42.503 --> 01:46.171
♪ Got a big black hole ♪

01:46.173 --> 01:49.909
♪ I've got a big black hole ♪

01:49.911 --> 01:54.046
♪ I've got a big black,
big black hole ♪

01:54.048 --> 01:58.050
♪ Got a big black hole
inside of me ♪

01:58.052 --> 02:00.052
♪ Got a ♪

02:01.656 --> 02:04.589
[ Crowd cheers ]

02:04.591 --> 02:09.194
♪<i> I know what you do</i>
<i> when you're sad and lonely</i> ♪

02:09.196 --> 02:11.464
[ Water splashes ]

02:11.466 --> 02:15.868
♪<i> I know what you do</i>
<i> when you love her only</i> ♪

02:15.870 --> 02:18.804
[ Music continues in distance ]

02:18.806 --> 02:21.607
♪<i> I know what you do when...</i> ♪

02:25.947 --> 02:34.487
♪♪

02:34.489 --> 02:43.162
♪♪

02:43.164 --> 02:51.504
♪♪

02:51.506 --> 03:00.245
♪♪

03:00.247 --> 03:01.948
A lotta burritos.

03:02.783 --> 03:04.249
Pope: Yeah,
it's for the skate park.

03:04.251 --> 03:06.118
Some of those kids
don't get much to eat.

03:10.457 --> 03:15.328
You know, the, um...
the skate-park-nonprofit idea?

03:15.330 --> 03:17.796
You don't have
to collect money or --

03:17.798 --> 03:19.999
J, we talked about it, man.
Okay, hear me out.

03:20.001 --> 03:21.734
We can --
We can put money through it,

03:21.736 --> 03:23.336
but structure it
as donations.
[ Cellphone vibrates ]

03:23.338 --> 03:25.137
We don't have to
take any money from anyone.

03:25.139 --> 03:27.272
Which means,
we can put like 100 grand,

03:27.274 --> 03:29.474
maybe more,
through it a year.

03:29.476 --> 03:32.144
Pope: Hey.

03:32.146 --> 03:33.812
Hey, there.

03:33.814 --> 03:35.815
You got my message?

03:37.284 --> 03:38.617
No, I was --

03:38.619 --> 03:39.952
I was [Chuckles]

03:39.954 --> 03:43.488
pretty surprised
to see you, too.

03:43.490 --> 03:45.224
Yeah?

03:45.226 --> 03:47.293
Sure, Carlsbad.

03:49.564 --> 03:51.364
Absolutely.

03:51.366 --> 03:54.700
7:30.
I'll see you there.

03:54.702 --> 03:56.235
Bye.

04:02.577 --> 04:04.443
J: Is that
your friend?

04:04.445 --> 04:05.378
Huh?

04:05.380 --> 04:08.313
On the phone,
was that --
Yeah.

04:08.315 --> 04:10.649
Well?
It was.

04:10.651 --> 04:13.652
Um...

04:13.654 --> 04:15.788
She's, uh...

04:15.790 --> 04:18.391
We're gonna have dinner.

04:18.393 --> 04:19.592
Good.

04:19.594 --> 04:20.793
[ Chuckles ]

04:20.795 --> 04:22.595
That's great.
Yeah.

04:22.597 --> 04:26.131
[ Sighs ] Holy shit.

04:26.133 --> 04:27.834
Shit.

04:30.938 --> 04:32.205
You know what, man?

04:32.207 --> 04:34.740
Print up the paperwork
for the nonprofit thing.

04:34.742 --> 04:36.075
I'll sign it.

04:36.077 --> 04:38.277
Really?
Yeah.

04:38.279 --> 04:39.544
[ Pan clatters ]

04:39.546 --> 04:41.047
I'm in.

04:44.685 --> 04:51.690
♪♪

04:51.692 --> 04:58.497
♪♪

04:58.499 --> 05:05.504
♪♪

05:05.506 --> 05:07.673
Jesus. Julia...

05:09.577 --> 05:11.110
What time is it?

05:11.112 --> 05:12.445
3:30.

05:12.447 --> 05:15.248
I had a dream about you.

05:15.250 --> 05:19.118
Are you sure
everyone's asleep?

05:19.120 --> 05:20.786
No.

05:20.788 --> 05:27.460
♪♪

05:27.462 --> 05:34.133
♪♪

05:34.135 --> 05:40.806
♪♪

05:40.808 --> 05:47.413
♪♪

05:49.150 --> 05:51.484
[ Groans ]
Oh, my God.

05:51.486 --> 05:54.219
What's the matter?

05:54.221 --> 05:56.155
Nothing.

05:56.157 --> 05:58.223
Just a little sore.

05:58.225 --> 05:59.758
Who'd you get
in a fight with?

05:59.760 --> 06:01.426
Some douchebag
at the beach?

06:01.428 --> 06:02.427
[ Keg clangs ]

06:02.429 --> 06:04.563
No, my brother
whupped my ass.

06:04.565 --> 06:07.300
You and Craig are
about the same age, right?

06:07.302 --> 06:09.168
Yeah.

06:09.170 --> 06:11.236
That must have been fun.

06:11.238 --> 06:15.040
Well, kid was an asshole,
and he still is.

06:15.042 --> 06:16.709
[ Keg scrapes ]

06:16.711 --> 06:17.843
[ Grunts ]

06:17.845 --> 06:20.579
[ Brittany moans ]

06:20.581 --> 06:21.780
Brittany: Yeah!

06:21.782 --> 06:23.648
Yeah!

06:23.650 --> 06:26.919
[ Exhales deeply ]

06:26.921 --> 06:30.389
[ Breathing heavily ]

06:30.391 --> 06:35.260
♪♪

06:35.262 --> 06:36.329
Wow!

06:36.331 --> 06:37.530
[ Sighs ]

06:37.532 --> 06:39.064
You okay?

06:39.066 --> 06:40.199
Craig: Yeah, yeah.

06:40.201 --> 06:42.868
Brittany:
You sticking around today?

06:42.870 --> 06:44.537
No, I gotta...

06:44.539 --> 06:47.139
refit the weights.

06:47.141 --> 06:49.542
And then I'm gonna take lunch
and see my kid.

06:49.544 --> 06:51.143
Your kid?
Yeah.

06:51.145 --> 06:53.546
I didn't know you had a kid.
Yeah.

06:53.548 --> 06:55.014
Boy or girl?

06:55.016 --> 06:57.082
Boy.
Wow.

06:57.084 --> 06:58.751
Is he, like, old?

06:58.753 --> 07:01.153
No.
Why would you say that?

07:01.155 --> 07:04.823
I don't know.
Just asking.

07:04.825 --> 07:07.960
I'm gonna take a shower,
okay?

07:09.164 --> 07:12.431
[ Children laugh, shout ]

07:12.433 --> 07:13.632
[ Baby coos ]

07:13.634 --> 07:15.268
[ Laughs ]

07:24.712 --> 07:26.479
[ Baby coos ]

07:37.392 --> 07:40.793
♪♪

07:40.795 --> 07:42.395
-[ Panting ]
-Hey! Look at me.

07:42.397 --> 07:44.397
Pay attention. Pay attention.
You know who I am.

07:44.399 --> 07:47.466
Right? Right?!
I tolerated this shit at first.

07:47.468 --> 07:50.403
Now I hear you're edging up,
got some big load coming in.

07:50.405 --> 07:51.670
That ain't gonna
work for me.

07:51.672 --> 07:53.338
You're gonna bring it all
to the park

07:53.340 --> 07:57.209
and put it in the trash cans
by the swing.

07:57.211 --> 07:59.678
Then we'll talk
about getting your kid back.

07:59.680 --> 08:00.813
[ Laughs ]

08:00.815 --> 08:03.148
No! No! No!

08:03.150 --> 08:05.884
[ Tires screech ]

08:05.886 --> 08:08.621
[ Screams ]

08:08.623 --> 08:09.955
[ Tires screech ]

08:09.957 --> 08:11.890
No! Nick!

08:11.892 --> 08:14.026
♪♪

08:14.028 --> 08:15.894
[ Engine starts ]

08:15.896 --> 08:18.097
[ Screams ]

08:18.099 --> 08:22.567
[ Tires screech ]

08:22.569 --> 08:28.573
♪♪

08:28.575 --> 08:34.447
♪♪

08:37.852 --> 08:40.819
[ Engine revs ]

08:40.821 --> 08:43.956
♪♪

08:43.958 --> 08:45.491
Deran.

08:45.493 --> 08:46.692
Office, now.

08:46.694 --> 08:48.560
What? Why?
Now! Let's go!

08:48.562 --> 08:49.495
Now!

08:49.497 --> 08:51.097
Shit.

08:51.099 --> 08:53.165
♪♪

08:53.167 --> 08:54.767
Guns, man.
You got guns?
What?

08:54.769 --> 08:56.769
-Guns! Do you have guns?
-What are you talking about?!

08:56.771 --> 08:58.170
What do you mean?
Yeah, yeah, I do.

08:58.172 --> 08:59.438
W-What's going on?
Jesus.

08:59.440 --> 09:01.307
Nick, man.
They -- they took him.

09:01.309 --> 09:02.708
What do you mean?
Who took him?

09:02.710 --> 09:04.242
Renn --
she got a big load in.

09:04.244 --> 09:06.178
And then they rolled her,
and then they took Nick

09:06.180 --> 09:08.915
so they could trade him
for the coke.

09:08.917 --> 09:10.916
Shit, man.

09:10.918 --> 09:12.518
Took my son, man!

09:12.520 --> 09:14.520
[ Glass clatters ]
Cut it off! Stop!

09:14.522 --> 09:17.589
Take a breath!
Slow down.

09:17.591 --> 09:19.525
Okay? Breathe.
We're gonna get him back.

09:19.527 --> 09:22.128
Is Renn okay?
Beat up, man,
but she's alright.

09:22.130 --> 09:23.329
Have you talked
to Pope or J?

09:23.331 --> 09:24.863
No, he's not answering
his phone.

09:24.865 --> 09:26.198
And I'm not calling J.

09:26.200 --> 09:27.599
Okay, okay. It's fine.
We'll get him back.

09:27.601 --> 09:29.535
The guns are in the safe.
I'll drive. Okay?

09:29.537 --> 09:30.736
Come on.

09:30.738 --> 09:32.338
[ Lock clicks ]

09:32.340 --> 09:34.006
Man: Alright.
Free food.

09:34.008 --> 09:35.808
Man #2:
Pass one over here.

09:35.810 --> 09:37.977
[ Indistinct conversations ]

09:44.284 --> 09:46.352
Yo, I see your plan, man.

09:46.354 --> 09:48.020
Fill everyone's stomachs

09:48.022 --> 09:49.688
so you can have
this thing to yourself?

09:49.690 --> 09:52.558
They looked hungry,
that's all.

09:52.560 --> 09:54.426
Yo, you win the lottery
or something, man?

09:54.428 --> 09:56.495
Ha!
You seem happy.

09:56.497 --> 09:59.365
No, I got
a date tonight.

09:59.367 --> 10:01.767
No shit.

10:01.769 --> 10:03.902
Who's the lucky lady?

10:03.904 --> 10:07.173
A friend from church.

10:07.175 --> 10:08.774
Oh, right on, dude!

10:08.776 --> 10:11.677
I used to have good luck
with church girls, man.

10:13.581 --> 10:15.247
Not like that, though.

10:15.249 --> 10:17.449
Like --
Where are you taking her?

10:17.451 --> 10:20.919
Uh, I don't know.
Some new place in Carlsbad.

10:20.921 --> 10:21.787
She picked it.

10:21.789 --> 10:23.589
Okay.

10:23.591 --> 10:24.523
Is it dark?

10:24.525 --> 10:26.124
What?

10:26.126 --> 10:27.793
It's got to be dark, man.

10:27.795 --> 10:29.261
And no loud music,

10:29.263 --> 10:32.398
or you can't have
a conversation.

10:32.400 --> 10:34.800
Has it got private tables?

10:34.802 --> 10:36.002
I don't know.

10:36.004 --> 10:37.736
Yo, find out, bro.

10:37.738 --> 10:40.739
Game changer.

10:40.741 --> 10:42.275
Come on, man.

10:54.689 --> 10:57.323
Is there something up
with your phone?

10:59.360 --> 11:02.428
I'm married, okay?

11:02.430 --> 11:04.697
And that thing --
that thing the other night?

11:04.699 --> 11:06.632
That was stupid
and dangerous,

11:06.634 --> 11:08.767
and it's never
gonna happen again.

11:08.769 --> 11:11.503
Okay, well, spend the day
with me.
Jesus, J.

11:11.505 --> 11:13.639
Hey, if you want me to go
to the grocery store,

11:13.641 --> 11:15.041
I need money.

11:16.444 --> 11:18.577
Um, Cindy.
This is J.

11:18.579 --> 11:20.713
He's a client
from the firm,

11:20.715 --> 11:23.181
and he's come to sign
some paperwork.

11:23.183 --> 11:26.118
J, this is my sister,
Cindy.

11:26.120 --> 11:27.453
Hey, Cindy.

11:27.455 --> 11:29.521
[ Chuckles ]
Hi, J.

11:29.523 --> 11:32.190
♪♪

11:32.192 --> 11:35.394
I want change --
and a receipt.

11:35.396 --> 11:38.264
Whatever.

11:38.266 --> 11:41.133
Bye, J.

11:41.135 --> 11:43.269
♪♪

11:43.271 --> 11:45.471
I didn't know you lived
with your sister.

11:45.473 --> 11:47.740
You don't know
a lot of things about me.

11:47.742 --> 11:51.877
I know that your husband's car
hasn't moved for a couple weeks.

11:51.879 --> 11:55.213
♪♪

11:55.215 --> 11:56.615
Come on.

11:56.617 --> 11:57.950
One day.

11:57.952 --> 12:01.019
♪♪

12:01.021 --> 12:03.622
Give me a few minutes.

12:03.624 --> 12:07.960
♪♪

12:07.962 --> 12:10.696
[ Engine turns off ]

12:10.698 --> 12:14.900
♪♪

12:14.902 --> 12:16.736
[ Cab door closes ]

12:17.972 --> 12:20.906
[ Men shout indistinctly ]

12:20.908 --> 12:22.408
Now.

12:22.710 --> 12:25.111
[ Beeps ]

12:25.113 --> 12:28.046
[ Sighs ]

12:28.048 --> 12:29.515
Are you bored?

12:29.517 --> 12:30.849
What?

12:30.851 --> 12:33.852
No.

12:33.854 --> 12:35.721
So, um...

12:35.723 --> 12:39.525
this is like a big RadioShack
or something?

12:39.527 --> 12:44.096
No, it's more like
a Target for electronics.

12:49.337 --> 12:51.604
You can barely
keep your eyes open.

12:51.606 --> 12:56.008
I just, you know,
couldn't sleep last night.

12:56.010 --> 12:58.945
You no-showed on the last job
I tried to bring you in on.

12:58.947 --> 13:01.681
Are you gonna shit the bed
on this one, too?

13:03.083 --> 13:05.551
No.

13:05.553 --> 13:06.686
Okay.

13:08.957 --> 13:11.089
I want you
to run this one.

13:11.091 --> 13:12.758
Really?

13:12.760 --> 13:15.161
Yeah, if you can get
a good night's sleep

13:15.163 --> 13:16.762
and keep your head
in the game.

13:16.764 --> 13:23.702
♪♪

13:23.704 --> 13:25.171
He's out.

13:25.173 --> 13:27.173
[ Watch beeps ]

13:27.175 --> 13:35.848
♪♪

13:35.850 --> 13:39.986
[<i> Announcer speaks Spanish</i>
<i> on TV</i> ]

13:39.988 --> 13:43.723
♪♪

13:51.265 --> 13:53.666
Pope: Excuse me.
You got a second?

13:53.668 --> 13:55.534
We don't open
until 2:00.

13:55.536 --> 13:57.203
[<i> Announcer continues</i>
<i> in Spanish</i> ]

13:57.205 --> 14:00.206
Can you turn that
down a little?

14:02.010 --> 14:04.142
[ TV mutes ]

14:04.144 --> 14:05.544
[ Sighing ] Oh, man.

14:05.546 --> 14:08.414
What can I help you with,
buddy?

14:08.416 --> 14:10.683
I got a date here
tonight.

14:10.685 --> 14:12.818
Okay.

14:12.820 --> 14:14.820
So, like...

14:14.822 --> 14:17.890
you got
any secluded tables?

14:17.892 --> 14:20.226
Eh, sorry.

14:20.228 --> 14:22.695
No.
No?

14:22.697 --> 14:25.631
What about, like,
maybe something that's removed

14:25.633 --> 14:31.503
from the bar area that's --
that's not so noisy.

14:31.505 --> 14:32.905
Anything like that?

14:32.907 --> 14:34.506
If you're looking
for the steak-house vibe,

14:34.508 --> 14:35.774
you might want to try AJ's
in Del Mar.

14:35.776 --> 14:39.177
I can't.
She picked this place.

14:39.179 --> 14:41.980
So if you had, like...

14:41.982 --> 14:45.784
a special table
that's a little bit quieter

14:45.786 --> 14:47.519
so we could, like,
hear each other,

14:47.521 --> 14:49.856
that would really
help me out.

14:53.527 --> 14:55.327
What time's your date?

14:55.329 --> 14:56.662
7:30.

14:56.664 --> 14:58.330
Okay, well,
I'm working dinner tonight,

14:58.332 --> 14:59.732
so just leave me your name.

14:59.734 --> 15:01.534
I'll find a mellow table
and try and hold it for you.

15:01.536 --> 15:04.403
And I'll see what I can do
about the music.

15:04.405 --> 15:06.305
No shit.

15:12.680 --> 15:15.681
Woman: Excuse me.

15:15.683 --> 15:17.283
I'm so sorry
to bother you.

15:17.285 --> 15:19.285
A-Are you Pope?

15:19.287 --> 15:22.154
Who's asking?

15:22.156 --> 15:23.489
I'm Louise.

15:23.491 --> 15:27.225
I followed you from
the skate park.

15:27.227 --> 15:28.794
I'm Taylor's mom.

15:31.832 --> 15:33.833
Have you seen him,
by any chance?

15:37.171 --> 15:40.038
No, not in a few days.

15:40.040 --> 15:42.441
Is he alright?

15:42.443 --> 15:44.977
I don't know.

15:44.979 --> 15:48.246
He came to the house,
and...

15:48.248 --> 15:50.783
we had a fight,
and I said some things.

15:50.785 --> 15:52.118
He really
looks up to you.

15:52.120 --> 15:53.852
He said that you took him
to the hospital,

15:53.854 --> 15:57.589
and that was
very kind of you.

15:57.591 --> 16:00.258
Do you think
you can help me look for him?

16:00.260 --> 16:05.698
♪♪

16:13.041 --> 16:15.708
Pope: I'll go in
and see if he's here.

16:21.782 --> 16:24.116
[ Keys jangle,
engine turns off ]

16:24.118 --> 16:25.918
I'll be right back.

16:25.920 --> 16:35.594
♪♪

16:35.596 --> 16:45.337
♪♪

16:45.339 --> 16:55.013
♪♪

16:55.015 --> 17:04.490
♪♪

17:04.492 --> 17:14.433
♪♪

17:14.435 --> 17:23.909
♪♪

17:23.911 --> 17:26.178
Hey, you seen
that Taylor kid?

17:26.180 --> 17:27.379
Mnm-mnm.

17:27.381 --> 17:28.847
[ Cellphone camera clicks ]

17:28.849 --> 17:30.849
Pope: Hey, any of you guys
seen that kid Taylor

17:30.851 --> 17:33.920
that fell down at the park
with the cut?

17:33.922 --> 17:35.788
You know who
I'm talking about?

17:35.790 --> 17:38.056
None of you?

17:38.058 --> 17:43.261
♪♪

17:43.263 --> 17:46.465
[ Sighs ] Sorry.
Nobody's seen him.

17:50.070 --> 17:51.804
Maybe we could go
look somewhere else.

17:51.806 --> 17:54.273
Did -- Did he mention any friend
or something maybe?

17:54.275 --> 17:55.942
[ Cellphone vibrates ]

17:55.944 --> 17:58.544
What?

17:58.546 --> 18:00.212
Do you need
to take a call?

18:00.214 --> 18:02.348
Hold on a sec.

18:02.350 --> 18:03.882
[ Car door slams ]

18:03.884 --> 18:06.284
[ Cellphone rings ]

18:06.286 --> 18:07.553
Hey.

18:07.555 --> 18:10.356
Hey, is everything alright?

18:10.358 --> 18:13.892
Um,

18:13.894 --> 18:16.762
look, I don't think
tonight's gonna work.

18:16.764 --> 18:20.232
Are you sure?
I mean, we could --

18:20.234 --> 18:22.635
we could start earlier or later
if you want or --

18:22.637 --> 18:24.703
or I could find
a new place.

18:24.705 --> 18:26.572
It's not that.
It's just --

18:28.776 --> 18:31.577
Look, this is hard,
Andrew.

18:31.579 --> 18:33.646
Look, I got to go.

18:33.648 --> 18:35.181
I'm helping this lady
find her kid.

18:35.183 --> 18:37.449
<i> I'm sorry. What?</i>
<i> It's super-loud in here.</i>

18:37.451 --> 18:38.651
I said, I got to go.

18:38.653 --> 18:41.521
I'm helping this lady
find her kid.

18:43.724 --> 18:46.258
You know what?
It's fine. I'm sorry.

18:46.260 --> 18:48.594
What?
<i> Just forget I said anything.</i>

18:48.596 --> 18:50.396
<i> I'll --</i>
<i> I'll see you at 7:30.</i>

18:50.398 --> 18:51.998
<i> I'm sorry.</i>
<i> I'm excited.</i>

18:52.000 --> 18:54.333
Okay. I'll --
I'll see you tonight.

18:54.335 --> 18:55.467
Okay.

18:55.469 --> 18:57.170
Alright.
Bye.

19:02.210 --> 19:03.876
I'm so sorry.

19:03.878 --> 19:06.345
You're probably busy,
and I'm holding you up.

19:06.347 --> 19:07.279
Do you think, is --

19:07.281 --> 19:09.215
is there another place
we could go and try --

19:09.217 --> 19:11.617
You know what? You're right.
I am really busy.

19:11.619 --> 19:13.819
Okay, fine.
We can just try maybe --

19:13.821 --> 19:14.953
This is a good day
for me.

19:14.955 --> 19:17.690
I don't have
many good days.

19:17.692 --> 19:19.692
You're disrupting it.

19:21.562 --> 19:24.963
Sure. We can just go --
I'm gonna take you
to your car now.

19:24.965 --> 19:26.933
[ Engine starts ]

19:32.172 --> 19:34.573
Oh. Here, baby.
I brought you these.

19:34.575 --> 19:36.709
I thought
you were up.

19:43.451 --> 19:44.983
Use up all
the hot water?

19:44.985 --> 19:46.184
Sorry.

19:46.186 --> 19:48.320
I think it's normal
for kids your age

19:48.322 --> 19:50.856
to take long showers.

19:50.858 --> 19:53.191
I was thinking.

19:53.193 --> 19:55.928
I-I don't care what you do
in the shower.

19:55.930 --> 19:58.865
That's the church's job...

19:58.867 --> 20:01.133
Pope.

20:01.135 --> 20:03.236
Baz started
calling me that.

20:05.406 --> 20:08.874
Have you noticed anything
different about...

20:08.876 --> 20:12.210
Julia and Baz lately?

20:12.212 --> 20:14.613
Like what?

20:14.615 --> 20:16.883
I don't know.

20:16.885 --> 20:19.551
They seem closer.

20:19.553 --> 20:21.087
No.

20:23.223 --> 20:25.624
They've been hanging out
a lot --

20:25.626 --> 20:28.894
without you.

20:28.896 --> 20:30.563
You know,
we're all family.

20:30.565 --> 20:32.631
I...

20:32.633 --> 20:35.201
I don't want you
to feel left out.

20:38.439 --> 20:40.006
I don't.

20:42.576 --> 20:44.043
That's good.

20:47.582 --> 20:54.586
♪♪

20:54.588 --> 20:57.590
Look at my
handsome boy.

20:57.592 --> 21:04.863
♪♪

21:04.865 --> 21:06.598
[ Door opens ]

21:06.600 --> 21:08.467
Craig: Renn.

21:08.469 --> 21:10.402
♪♪

21:10.404 --> 21:12.805
[ Man speaks Spanish ]

21:12.807 --> 21:18.544
♪♪

21:18.546 --> 21:24.350
♪♪

21:24.352 --> 21:25.484
[ Sighs ] Craig.

21:25.486 --> 21:27.753
♪♪

21:27.755 --> 21:29.155
[ Exhales shakily ]
Craig, Craig...

21:29.157 --> 21:32.891
Do you know who
did this, Renn?

21:32.893 --> 21:33.960
Craig...

21:33.962 --> 21:36.695
Do you know
who did this?

21:36.697 --> 21:38.697
♪♪

21:38.699 --> 21:40.299
God damn it, Renn.

21:40.301 --> 21:41.834
I told you that this
would happen.
I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

21:41.836 --> 21:43.369
Craig.

21:43.371 --> 21:46.172
Please.

21:46.174 --> 21:48.907
It's alright.
Alright, look.

21:48.909 --> 21:50.176
I'm gonna get our son back,
okay?

21:50.178 --> 21:51.777
I'm gonna come with you guys,
and I'll fix it.

21:51.779 --> 21:53.846
I promise.
Hey, hey, hey, hey.

21:53.848 --> 21:55.781
Renn, look at me.

21:55.783 --> 21:57.783
Look at me.

21:57.785 --> 21:59.585
You stay here, alright?

21:59.587 --> 22:01.854
Can you do that for me?

22:01.856 --> 22:03.990
Can you do that?

22:03.992 --> 22:05.391
I promise you,

22:05.393 --> 22:08.260
I'm gonna get our son back,
alright?

22:08.262 --> 22:16.002
♪♪

22:16.004 --> 22:18.604
Who did this?

22:18.606 --> 22:21.007
Cole Lidden.
Cole Lidden?

22:21.009 --> 22:23.141
Nazi dude,
white-power tats.

22:23.143 --> 22:25.011
Moves weight
around here.

22:25.013 --> 22:27.613
Okay.
Where do we find him?

22:27.615 --> 22:29.615
[ Sighs ]

22:29.617 --> 22:30.949
I know a dealer
he works with.

22:30.951 --> 22:32.218
Alright.
Lead us, show us.

22:32.220 --> 22:34.620
-Let's go. Come on.
-Let's go. Lead the way.

22:34.622 --> 22:37.023
♪♪

22:37.025 --> 22:39.625
Wow!
You're a natural.

22:39.627 --> 22:41.027
Texas girl.

22:41.029 --> 22:42.961
What do you expect?

22:42.963 --> 22:46.032
How long has your sister
lived with you?

22:46.034 --> 22:47.834
Sorry if, uh...

22:49.169 --> 22:51.304
...if she seemed rude.

22:52.040 --> 22:53.772
She seemed high.

22:53.774 --> 22:55.908
♪♪

22:55.910 --> 22:58.511
Um, my mom
was an addict.

23:01.315 --> 23:02.314
Did she --

23:02.316 --> 23:04.450
Did she ever get clean?

23:04.452 --> 23:06.585
No.

23:06.587 --> 23:12.458
♪♪

23:12.460 --> 23:18.330
♪♪

23:18.332 --> 23:20.866
It's hard.

23:20.868 --> 23:22.668
You know, at first,
you're pissed,

23:22.670 --> 23:24.336
and then you accept it,

23:24.338 --> 23:27.473
and then you're just a caregiver
and then you forget

23:27.475 --> 23:29.675
you're supposed to have
your own life.

23:29.677 --> 23:32.878
♪♪

23:32.880 --> 23:36.882
She's my sister.

23:36.884 --> 23:39.017
I'm, uh...

23:39.019 --> 23:42.621
I'm gonna help her
through it.

23:42.623 --> 23:44.556
[ Axe clangs ]

23:44.558 --> 23:45.958
Can we go?

23:45.960 --> 23:49.628
I'm, uh...
getting hungry.

23:49.630 --> 23:51.097
Um...

23:51.099 --> 23:52.498
yeah, sure.

23:52.500 --> 23:55.701
Yeah.

23:55.703 --> 23:58.236
Look, the drivers
always go inside.

23:58.238 --> 23:59.972
They're never in
for less than 3 minutes.

23:59.974 --> 24:02.040
Plenty of time
to lift a truck.

24:02.042 --> 24:04.176
I need two guys
on the truck

24:04.178 --> 24:06.712
and a lookout.

24:06.714 --> 24:08.914
Really good job, baby.

24:08.916 --> 24:10.316
Well done.

24:10.318 --> 24:12.118
I gotta go pick up
Craig and Deran from school.

24:12.120 --> 24:14.253
Can I have your keys?
Yeah.

24:17.057 --> 24:18.925
You gonna come with me?

24:18.927 --> 24:21.527
Uh, no,
I'm gonna hang out here.

24:21.529 --> 24:25.397
♪♪

24:25.399 --> 24:26.999
[ Scoffs ]

24:27.001 --> 24:28.801
Bye, Julia.

24:28.803 --> 24:38.344
♪♪

24:38.346 --> 24:40.813
[ Truck doors close ]
[ Brakes squeak ]

24:40.815 --> 24:43.950
♪♪

24:43.952 --> 24:45.484
What's up, uso?

24:45.486 --> 24:47.486
Can I get an 8?
8 what?

24:47.488 --> 24:49.355
8 years
'cause you a cop?

24:49.357 --> 24:51.690
I ain't a cop.
Hey, shit, take it.

24:51.692 --> 24:52.825
I don't want to get shot.

24:52.827 --> 24:54.160
I ain't gonna run.
Let's go.

24:54.162 --> 24:55.694
Craig: Come on.
You're coming with us.

24:55.696 --> 24:57.496
Let's move.

24:57.498 --> 25:00.299
♪♪

25:00.301 --> 25:02.168
Open the door.
The hell are you doing?

25:02.170 --> 25:04.036
Taking him.
Taking me where?

25:04.038 --> 25:05.704
We're gonna go and see
your buddy Cole.

25:05.706 --> 25:08.440
Cole? Oh, hell --
You're out of your mind!
Get in the car.

25:08.442 --> 25:09.775
Get in the car
and follow us!

25:09.777 --> 25:10.909
Come on.

25:10.911 --> 25:12.511
Sit down!

25:12.513 --> 25:14.913
♪♪

25:14.915 --> 25:17.049
[ Tires screech ]

25:17.051 --> 25:18.451
Craig: Alright.
Where are we going?

25:21.922 --> 25:23.055
-Penny: Well?
-J: Okay.

25:23.057 --> 25:24.323
Penny: Texas girl,
I told you.

25:24.325 --> 25:26.325
From the kitchen --
Kobe beef sliders

25:26.327 --> 25:28.994
and the chef's take
on chile verde nachos.

25:28.996 --> 25:31.930
Thank you.

25:31.932 --> 25:33.266
Damn, you<i> were</i> hungry.

25:33.268 --> 25:34.533
They keep bringing it out,

25:34.535 --> 25:36.401
so I might as well
keep eating it.

25:36.403 --> 25:38.804
Uh-huh.

25:38.806 --> 25:41.340
Sorry I was a bitch
earlier.

25:41.342 --> 25:43.408
What? No. No.
It's all good.

25:43.410 --> 25:45.344
It's been a while
since I've been out

25:45.346 --> 25:48.347
to have some fun.

25:48.349 --> 25:52.084
So, why do they love
you here so much?

25:52.086 --> 25:55.087
Um, well, my family
has a stake in this place.

25:55.089 --> 25:58.090
We helped them
get set up.

25:58.092 --> 26:02.161
That's actually one
of the owners right there.

26:02.163 --> 26:03.963
I'll be right back.
I'm gonna --

26:03.965 --> 26:05.965
I'm gonna go say "thanks"
to the chef.

26:05.967 --> 26:07.300
Okay.

26:07.302 --> 26:10.303
[ Indistinct conversations ]

26:16.311 --> 26:18.110
It's pretty busy
out there.

26:18.112 --> 26:20.112
Yeah.
It could be busier.

26:20.114 --> 26:21.780
You got enough to eat?

26:21.782 --> 26:23.516
You're late.

26:23.518 --> 26:24.850
Right.

26:24.852 --> 26:27.520
Well, I'm doing my best
to keep you happy out there.

26:27.522 --> 26:30.723
You think you can just pay us
in free appetizers?

26:30.725 --> 26:32.325
Dude,
we're getting there.

26:32.327 --> 26:34.360
No need to call in
your uncle.

26:37.332 --> 26:38.998
Drew: Oh!
You broke my nose!

26:39.000 --> 26:42.267
You came to us, remember?

26:42.269 --> 26:44.937
I'm sorry.
No, don't be sorry.

26:44.939 --> 26:46.605
Be on time.

26:46.607 --> 26:47.806
Okay.

26:47.808 --> 26:50.609
♪♪

26:50.611 --> 26:51.476
[ Groans ]

26:51.478 --> 26:57.282
[<i> Down tempo music plays</i> ]

26:57.284 --> 26:59.084
I left you one.

26:59.086 --> 27:00.152
Thank you.

27:00.154 --> 27:03.288
[ Chuckles ]

27:03.290 --> 27:06.625
What did you
get on your sleeve?

27:06.627 --> 27:07.960
Oh, shit.

27:07.962 --> 27:09.628
God damn it.

27:09.630 --> 27:12.497
Must have been ketchup
or something from the kitchen.

27:12.499 --> 27:15.034
[ Indistinct conversations ]

27:15.036 --> 27:16.902
Ugh!

27:16.904 --> 27:19.572
[ Sighs ] Do you
want another drink?

27:19.574 --> 27:21.240
Sure.

27:24.311 --> 27:26.712
Cole lives in there?

27:26.714 --> 27:28.047
No.

27:28.049 --> 27:29.248
I said this is
where he hangs out.

27:29.250 --> 27:31.316
Yeah?
You been inside?

27:31.318 --> 27:33.052
I picked up from here
this morning.

27:33.054 --> 27:34.853
Where's
the front door lead to?

27:34.855 --> 27:37.056
Stairway going up.

27:37.058 --> 27:39.658
Up to what?

27:39.660 --> 27:43.328
Meth lab on the left,
and then a lounge

27:43.330 --> 27:46.265
and a couple bedrooms
down the hall.

27:48.469 --> 27:50.736
There's a car stashed
in the back under a tarp.

27:50.738 --> 27:52.337
Looks like Renn's Jeep.
Okay.

27:52.339 --> 27:54.339
Get out of the car.

27:54.341 --> 27:56.675
Craig: Out.
[ Car doors close ]

27:56.677 --> 27:58.611
We got it from here.

27:58.613 --> 28:01.814
Anybody shows up after us,
lay down the horn.

28:01.816 --> 28:04.349
This guy does anything stupid,
you can shoot him.

28:04.351 --> 28:05.818
Give me the shotgun.

28:05.820 --> 28:11.556
♪♪

28:11.558 --> 28:12.758
You okay?
Ready?

28:12.760 --> 28:14.427
Let's be smart.
We'll get him.

28:14.429 --> 28:15.694
Let's go. Come on.
Let's go.

28:15.696 --> 28:22.768
♪♪

28:22.770 --> 28:24.036
Yeah, let's go.

28:24.038 --> 28:30.375
♪♪

28:30.377 --> 28:32.511
[<i> Metal music plays</i>
<i> in distance</i> ]

28:32.513 --> 28:40.786
♪♪

28:40.788 --> 28:48.794
♪♪

28:48.796 --> 28:56.869
♪♪

28:56.871 --> 29:05.144
♪♪

29:05.146 --> 29:07.880
[ Lock clicks ]

29:07.882 --> 29:17.623
♪♪

29:17.625 --> 29:27.099
♪♪

29:27.101 --> 29:28.634
Shh, shh!

29:28.636 --> 29:32.437
Shh! Shh! Shh!
Where's the kid?

29:32.439 --> 29:33.906
Where's the kid?
Quiet.

29:33.908 --> 29:41.113
♪♪

29:41.115 --> 29:48.120
♪♪

29:48.122 --> 29:52.525
[ Music plays faintly,
indistinct conversations ]

29:53.460 --> 29:54.793
Right this way.

29:54.795 --> 29:56.128
Thanks.
Yep.

29:56.130 --> 29:57.330
Hey.

29:57.332 --> 29:59.131
Sorry. Traffic.
Hey.

29:59.133 --> 30:00.333
Hi.

30:00.335 --> 30:03.068
Oh, that's okay.
I was -- I --

30:03.070 --> 30:05.371
I just got here.
Alright.

30:13.014 --> 30:16.816
[ Indistinct conversations ]

30:22.089 --> 30:24.623
Thank you.

30:24.625 --> 30:27.960
[ Clears throat ]

30:27.962 --> 30:30.363
Thanks for coming.

30:30.365 --> 30:32.631
<i> I</i> invited<i> you.</i>

30:32.633 --> 30:37.170
Yeah, okay, well...
thanks anyways.

30:41.175 --> 30:42.507
You look good?
Oh...

30:42.509 --> 30:44.977
You look like
you've been working out.

30:44.979 --> 30:46.579
So do you.

30:46.581 --> 30:49.915
I mean, you look --
you look good.

30:49.917 --> 30:51.350
You look great.

30:54.922 --> 30:59.058
We got a good table.
It's so loud over there.

30:59.060 --> 31:01.727
It's nice.

31:01.729 --> 31:03.929
[ Metal music continues ]

31:03.931 --> 31:12.938
♪♪

31:12.940 --> 31:14.073
Deran: Locked?

31:14.075 --> 31:15.874
Go around.

31:15.876 --> 31:17.209
Cover me.

31:17.211 --> 31:23.749
♪♪

31:23.751 --> 31:25.218
Hey!

31:25.220 --> 31:32.291
♪♪

31:32.293 --> 31:33.426
[ Nick cries ]
Don't move.

31:33.428 --> 31:34.960
Don't move.
Don't move!

31:34.962 --> 31:36.896
You don't move.
Put it down, man.

31:36.898 --> 31:40.365
Who the hell are you?
Back away from the kid.

31:40.367 --> 31:41.700
Drop the gun
and get out of here.

31:41.702 --> 31:43.836
I mean it!
Put the gun down!

31:43.838 --> 31:44.904
Hey, Deran! Deran.
Get out of here!

31:44.906 --> 31:46.839
Do not shoot, Deran!
Get out of here!

31:46.841 --> 31:48.974
You keep walking,
and I'll kill you.

31:48.976 --> 31:50.042
Hey!

31:50.044 --> 31:55.114
♪♪

31:55.116 --> 31:57.382
Stay there!

31:57.384 --> 32:00.853
Deran?

32:00.855 --> 32:02.321
Deran.

32:02.323 --> 32:03.522
Deran!

32:03.524 --> 32:08.261
[ Panting ]

32:08.263 --> 32:10.596
Yeah, I'm okay.
I'm okay.

32:10.598 --> 32:13.866
Don't move.
Get Nick.

32:13.868 --> 32:17.336
Alright.

32:17.338 --> 32:18.603
Hi, baby.

32:18.605 --> 32:19.939
It's okay.
Craig: Take him out of here.

32:19.941 --> 32:22.607
Come on. Let's go.
He's okay.

32:22.609 --> 32:23.943
[ Laughs ]

32:23.945 --> 32:26.279
Take Nick out of here,
Deran.

32:26.281 --> 32:28.614
Come on. It's okay.
It's okay.

32:28.616 --> 32:30.683
This ain't over.
[ Laughs ]

32:40.161 --> 32:44.096
Come on.
Help me with this.

32:44.098 --> 32:47.632
[ Sighs ]

32:47.634 --> 32:52.037
I was afraid you weren't gonna
show up to this.

32:52.039 --> 32:54.307
I was pretty nervous.

32:54.309 --> 32:55.708
Yeah.

32:55.710 --> 32:57.977
Um...

32:57.979 --> 33:00.179
I mean,
I thought about not coming.

33:00.181 --> 33:02.014
Um...

33:04.986 --> 33:09.388
But I wanted
to see you again.

33:09.390 --> 33:11.657
And, um...

33:14.261 --> 33:17.363
...I owe you an apology.

33:19.266 --> 33:20.933
I mean, I expect God

33:20.935 --> 33:23.736
to forgive me
the way He promised,

33:23.738 --> 33:27.006
but I know that He asks
that I do the same.

33:27.008 --> 33:30.075
[ Sighs ]

33:30.077 --> 33:32.477
And I judged you.

33:32.479 --> 33:35.214
[ Sighs ]

33:35.216 --> 33:38.017
When what I should have done
was forgiven you.

33:40.355 --> 33:44.056
It's God's place to judge you,
not mine, not anyone's.

33:46.961 --> 33:49.028
Forgive me.

33:49.030 --> 33:50.363
Please forgive me.

33:50.365 --> 33:53.298
Oh, you didn't do
anything wrong.

33:53.300 --> 33:55.100
I did.

33:55.102 --> 34:02.975
♪♪

34:02.977 --> 34:11.116
♪♪

34:11.118 --> 34:13.986
How's Renn doing?

34:13.988 --> 34:16.989
Yeah. She's alright, man.
She's asleep.

34:16.991 --> 34:26.531
♪♪

34:26.533 --> 34:27.800
Take my car.

34:27.802 --> 34:29.068
You don't have
to do that.

34:29.070 --> 34:31.536
No, it's fine.
I need to --

34:31.538 --> 34:34.073
I'm gonna take a walk
or something.

34:34.075 --> 34:35.741
Take 'em.

34:35.743 --> 34:42.014
♪♪

34:42.016 --> 34:43.616
Watch the rib,
watch the...

34:43.618 --> 34:45.150
Thank you, man.

34:45.152 --> 34:50.222
♪♪

34:50.224 --> 34:52.491
Go be with Nick.

34:52.493 --> 34:53.892
I'll see you tomorrow.

34:53.894 --> 34:55.094
Yeah.

34:55.096 --> 35:00.365
♪♪

35:00.367 --> 35:03.235
Penny: I wish
I brought my suit.

35:03.237 --> 35:05.170
You don't need one.

35:05.172 --> 35:07.106
Yeah, 'cause that
wouldn't be awkward

35:07.108 --> 35:09.241
the next time
I see your uncles.

35:09.243 --> 35:10.575
Everybody does it.

35:10.577 --> 35:12.712
[ Snorts, laughs ]

35:16.517 --> 35:17.783
So, are you gonna tell me

35:17.785 --> 35:22.121
about the stake you have
in that restaurant?

35:22.123 --> 35:24.056
♪♪

35:24.058 --> 35:26.859
Do you really
want to know?

35:26.861 --> 35:29.328
I don't know. Do I?

35:29.330 --> 35:32.397
♪♪

35:32.399 --> 35:33.932
Am I talking to someone

35:33.934 --> 35:38.604
who works for, uh,
Neimann, Livingston, and Kohl?

35:38.606 --> 35:40.005
We are a fiduciary.

35:40.007 --> 35:42.607
But you're
not a lawyer.

35:42.609 --> 35:44.409
Fair enough.

35:44.411 --> 35:47.412
♪♪

35:47.414 --> 35:49.081
Is that why you wanted me
to come today,

35:49.083 --> 35:54.419
a peek-behind-the-curtain,
flinch-test sort of thing?

35:54.421 --> 35:57.156
I wanted you to come today
'cause I like you.

35:57.158 --> 36:02.828
♪♪

36:02.830 --> 36:05.498
I like you, too.

36:05.500 --> 36:10.836
♪♪

36:10.838 --> 36:13.438
This house must have been great
growing up.

36:13.440 --> 36:19.244
♪♪

36:19.246 --> 36:25.050
♪♪

36:25.052 --> 36:29.722
Pope: You gonna...
let me pay next time?

36:29.724 --> 36:33.192
Amy: As friends?

36:33.194 --> 36:34.459
Of course.

36:34.461 --> 36:35.728
As friends.

36:38.065 --> 36:39.598
Yeah, I think
I'm ready for that.

36:39.600 --> 36:41.300
Okay.

36:45.806 --> 36:48.273
I'm sorry.
I-I waited as long as I could.

36:48.275 --> 36:50.343
Um, I'm -- I'm Louise.

36:50.345 --> 36:52.878
Pope was helping me
look for my son earlier today.

36:52.880 --> 36:54.813
Oh, yeah.
He told me about that.

36:54.815 --> 36:57.950
I'm Amy.
Did you find him?

36:57.952 --> 36:58.951
I'm sorry.
No.

36:58.953 --> 37:01.420
I-I left my phone
in your car,

37:01.422 --> 37:02.621
and I thought I lost it,

37:02.623 --> 37:03.889
but then I, um --
what was it? --

37:03.891 --> 37:05.558
I figured out a way
to locate it,

37:05.560 --> 37:07.693
and it's in your car.

37:07.695 --> 37:09.228
You're on a date.
I'm so sorry.

37:09.230 --> 37:10.563
No, no, no, no.
It's fine.

37:10.565 --> 37:11.697
It's fine.
I should go anyway.

37:11.699 --> 37:13.699
Um, go help her.

37:13.701 --> 37:15.100
What? Are you sure?

37:15.102 --> 37:16.102
Yeah.

37:18.773 --> 37:21.174
Alright.
Thank you for dinner.

37:21.176 --> 37:27.980
♪♪

37:27.982 --> 37:29.648
I'll call you, okay?
Drive safe.

37:29.650 --> 37:31.784
Alright.
Hey, good luck.

37:31.786 --> 37:33.452
Thank you.

37:33.454 --> 37:35.854
♪♪

37:35.856 --> 37:37.856
[ Car door opens ]

37:37.858 --> 37:39.324
[ Car door closes ]

37:39.326 --> 37:45.931
[ Engine starts ]

37:45.933 --> 37:49.735
She's beautiful --
your girlfriend.

37:49.737 --> 37:52.471
No, she's just a friend.

37:52.473 --> 37:59.078
♪♪

37:59.080 --> 38:05.484
♪♪

38:05.486 --> 38:11.891
♪♪

38:11.893 --> 38:13.492
Get your phone.

38:13.494 --> 38:20.433
♪♪

38:20.435 --> 38:27.372
♪♪

38:27.374 --> 38:28.441
Oh, wow.

38:28.443 --> 38:29.842
[ Sighs ]

38:29.844 --> 38:32.245
What a relief.

38:32.247 --> 38:33.912
Yeah, thank God.

38:33.914 --> 38:36.581
♪♪

38:36.583 --> 38:38.250
Yeah.
Thank you.

38:38.252 --> 38:41.654
♪♪

38:41.656 --> 38:43.322
Thank you
for everything today.

38:43.324 --> 38:48.861
♪♪

38:48.863 --> 38:50.863
Sorry about your date.

38:50.865 --> 38:55.134
♪♪

38:55.136 --> 38:59.238
